name: FRigUnit_SphereTraceByTraceChannel
doc:
Sweeps a sphere against the world and return the first blocking hit using a specific channel. Target objects can have different object types, but they need to have the same trace channel set to "block" in their collision response settings.
You can create custom trace channels in Project Setting - Collision.

Start: Start of the trace in rig / global space
End: End of the trace in rig / global space
TraceChannel: The 'channel' that this trace is in, used to determine which components to hit
Radius: Radius of the sphere to use for sweeping / tracing
bHit: Returns true if there was a hit
HitLocation: Hit location in rig / global Space
HitNormal: Hit normal in rig / global Space
